3988	985	The always policy is the simplest. It always restarts a stopped container\nunless it has been explicitly stopped.\nHowever, if you restart the Docker daemon, the container will be\nautomatically restarted when the daemon comes back up.	text	txt	2024-07-28 10:06:19.691226	1
