4089	1032	Managing your swarm and applications declaratively is a great way to prevent the need to recover from a backup.\nFor example, storing conguration objects outside of the swarm in a source code repository will enable you to redeploy things like networks, services, secrets and other objects.\nHowever, managing your environment declaratively and strictly using source control repos requires discipline.	text	txt	2024-07-28 10:06:34.184638	1
