4168	1061	1. **Docker commands:** run a container and input the commands to create new image with `docker commit`.\n2. **Dockerfile:** Build from a known base image, and specify the build with a limited set of simple commands.\n3. **Dockerfile and configuration management (CM) tool:** Same as Dockerfile, but you hand over control of the build to a more sophisticated CM tool.\n4. **Scratch image and import a set of files:** From an empty image, import a TAR file with the required files.	text	txt	2024-07-28 10:06:45.608462	1
