5120	1480	With `mutex_lock()`, your task will be put in an uninterruptible sleep state (`TASK_UNINTERRUPTIBLE`) while waiting for the mutex to be released if it is held by another task.	text	txt	2024-07-28 10:09:25.883232	3
5121	1480	`mutex_lock_interruptible()` will put your task in an interruptible sleep state, in which the sleep can be interrupted by any signal.	text	txt	2024-07-28 10:09:25.905289	4
5122	1480	`mutex_lock_killable()` will allow your sleeping task to be interrupted only by signals that actually kill the task.	text	txt	2024-07-28 10:09:25.925568	5
