5132	1484	It may be cheaper to use spinlocks for very small critical sections since the spinlock only suspends the scheduler and starts spinning, compared to the cost of using a mutex, which needs to suspend the current task and insert it into the mutex's wait queue, requiring the scheduler to switch to another task and rescheduling the sleeping task once the mutex is released.	text	txt	2024-07-28 10:09:27.244425	1
